        <headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued May 18 at 1:49AM MDT until May 18 at 6:00PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Wet snow expected. Total snow accumulations up to 2 inches
up to pass level, with 3 to 8 inches expected over the higher
terrain.

* WHERE...Gallatin and Madison County Mountains and Centennial
Mountains.

* WHEN...From 6 AM this morning to 6 PM MDT this evening.

* IMPACTS...Cold, snowy, and wet outdoor recreation conditions
expected. Roads may become slushy and slippery, especially
secondary roadways in the mountains.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Outdoor recreationists should take extra
precautions and be properly dressed to avoid hypothermia from the
cold and wet conditions.
</description>
        <instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling. The latest road
conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1 or visiting the MDT Road
Report website.</instruction>
